    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add your <strong>white long grain</strong> <strong>rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, transfer the rice to a plate and spread it out flat to help it cool down</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salt-and-pepper-chicken-breast-with-egg-fried-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>cornflour</strong> to a bowl along with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, your <strong>five-spice mix </strong>and a generous grind of<strong> black pepper </strong>and mix it all together</p><p>Add your <strong>chicken </strong>to the bowl and give everything a good mix up until all the chicken is coated</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salt-and-pepper-chicken-breast-with-egg-fried-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very large drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>coated chicken </strong>and cook for 5-6 min on each side until golden and crispy and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salt-and-pepper-chicken-breast-with-egg-fried-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, trim, then roughly chop your <strong>spring onions</strong> into batons</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Finely slice your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> into rounds</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salt-and-pepper-chicken-breast-with-egg-fried-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is crispy, add the <strong>spring onion batons</strong>, most of the <strong>chilli rounds </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min until fragrant</p><p>Once done, transfer everything to a plate (save the pan!) and set aside until serving \u2013 this is your <strong>salt & pepper chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salt-and-pepper-chicken-breast-with-egg-fried-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>cooled rice</strong>, your <strong>blanched peas</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong> and <strong>soy sauce</strong>, then stir everything together until combined and cook for 2-3 min</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salt-and-pepper-chicken-breast-with-egg-fried-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once combined, push the rice to one side of the pan and crack your <strong>egg[s]</strong> into the other side</p><p>Stir the<strong> egg[s]</strong> with a wooden spoon to break the yolk[s] and cook for 1-2 min until it resembles scrambled egg, then mix it all through the rice \u2013 this is your <strong>egg fried rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salt-and-pepper-chicken-breast-with-egg-fried-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> salt & pepper chicken</strong> over the <strong>egg fried rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining chilli rounds </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
